  "text": "to construct a disclose-if-zero protocol. As commonly used additively homomorphic encryption schemes have a composite plaintext space Z N , extra care is required to address cases when x is non-trivial factor of N . The corresponding protocol together with standard extensions can be found in [CITATION_1] . In brief, the protocol use a specific function pair (encode, decode) to double encrypt secrets. The restriction ∀s ∈ S : decode(encode(s)) ≡ s .",
